Title : Eastern Orthodoxy in Austria
Text : '''Eastern Orthodoxy in Austria''' is the totality of all [[Eastern Orthodox Church]]es in [[Austria]]. Most churches belong to the [[Ecumenical Council of Churches in Austria]].

There is around 400,000 to 450,000 Orthodox believers in Austria as of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.romfea.news/austria-450000-orthodox-believers-live-in-the-country/|title=Austria: 450,000 Orthodox believers live in the country|date=2019-03-12|website=Romfea News|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-12}}</ref>

== Eastern Orthodox Churches in Austria ==
* [[Bulgarian Orthodox Church]]: Parish of St. Ivan Rilski, [[Vienna]]
* [[Greek Orthodox Metropolis of Austria]]: 12 parishes, of which three are in Vienna
* [[Greek Orthodox Church of Antioch]]: One parish in Vienna
* [[Romanian Orthodox Church]]: Five parishes, of which only one is in Vienna
* [[Russian Orthodox Church]]: Parish of St. Nicholas, Vienna
* [[Serbian Orthodox Eparchy of Austria and Switzerland]]: Four Parishes, of which two are in Vienna, including Parish of St. Sava

